[[Image:White Knife.png|thumb|right|200px|A map showing the location of the White Knife on the continent of Westeros.]]

The '''White Knife''' is a river in [[the North]]. It consists of two rivers, one originating in [[Long Lake]] and the other in hills to the east, which come together north-east of [[Winterfell]]. The river runs south into [[the Bite]], with the city of [[White Harbor]] located at its mouth.&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/locations/Moat_Cailin/ HBO viewers guide, season 2 map, Moat Cailin entry]&lt;/ref&gt;

The White Knife was infested with pirates, until the [[Stark]] [[King in the North|Kings of Winter]] drove them away.&lt;ref&gt;[[House Bolton (Histories &amp; Lore)]]&lt;/ref&gt;
